HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 364
By Mitchell
A RESOLUTION to honor TailGate Brewery on the occasion of its
tenth anniversary in Nashville.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly are pleased to recognize a local
Tennessee business that has grown leaps and bounds to earn distinction as one of the best
craft beer breweries in the nation; and
WHEREAS, in February 2025, TailGate Brewery celebrated its tenth anniversary in
Nashville, after owner Wes Keegan relocated his company from San Diego, California, in the fall
of 2014; and
WHEREAS, the seven-acre TailGate Brewery headquarters opened in West Nashville in
February 2015, and the rest, as they say, is history; and
WHEREAS, from the humble beginnings of a one-man operation with no outside
investors, TailGate Brewery has grown to include 250 team members and nine breweries in
Tennessee, and the original location now features a fifty-barrel brewing system that produces
more than 300 recipes per year; and
WHEREAS, the second TailGate location opened on Music Row in 2016, followed by
new locations in East Nashville in 2018, Nashville International Airport in 2021, Germantown,
Hendersonville, and Chattanooga in 2022, South Nashville in 2023, and Murfreesboro in 2024;
and
WHEREAS, these nine breweries have three essential elements in common: cold,
creative beer, delicious pizza, and friendly customer service; and
WHEREAS, although he has attained great success in the past ten years, Mr. Keegan
remains committed to his mission of owning and operating the best craft beer brewery in
Tennessee; and
