WHEREAS, Mr. Keegan's business model centers on people, and he wisely credits his
employees as key players in TailGate's growth and overall success; and
WHEREAS, TailGate has been able to hire and retain employees in a tight labor market
because of the company's ongoing investment in its team members; and
WHEREAS, in July 2022, TailGate began paying 100 percent of health-care benefits for
every one of its employees, thus achieving a longtime goal; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Keegan was inspired to offer this rare industry benefit to his employees
by the example of his late father, who died too young, in large part because he did not have
access to health care; and
WHEREAS, an icon in Nashville for ten years, TailGate Brewery is deserving of our
recognition as a bastion of great beer and even better company; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor owner Wes Keegan and the management and employees of
TailGate Brewery on the occasion of the brewery's tenth anniversary in Nashville and
congratulate them on growing their business to include nine locations in Tennessee.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
